-- BES seesaws in volatile trade after suspension lifted
-- 
-- Fri Jul 11, 2014 06:51AM EDT
-- None



LISBON, July 11 (Reuters) - Shares in Banco Espirito Santo opened higher, but then dropped again on Friday following the end of a suspension after the bank told investors that losses on loans to the troubled business empire of its founding family will not put its capital at risk.

Trading in the stock that had fallen 17 percent on Thursday before being suspended resumed at 1030 GMT on Friday, with the shares jumping 11 percent higher. But they soon reversed gains to trade 1.6 percent lower at 0.5010 euros by 1040 GMT.